To find (A x B) ∪ (A x {c}), we first need to find the Cartesian products A x B and A x {c}.

A x B = {(1, a), (1, b), (2, a), (2, b), (3, a), (3, b)}

A x {c} = {(1, c), (2, c), (3, c)}

Now, we find the union of these two sets:

(A x B) ∪ (A x {c}) = {(1, a), (1, b), (2, a), (2, b), (3, a), (3, b), (1, c), (2, c), (3, c)}
